The paper deals with data structures for supporting queries on compressed text, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The use of string attractors and LZ77 compression suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and compression (cs.CC) may also be relevant sub-categories. The paper also discusses dictionary compression and tree representations, which are topics in data compression (cs.DC) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
